trans-unit.source: Represents a merged <xref href="System.Printing.PrintTicket"></xref> that is guaranteed to be viable, with a report of any settings that were changed to make it viable.
If the initial <xref:System.Printing.PrintTicket> asks for printing functionality that the printer does not support, the printer driver resolves all conflicts in order to produce a viable ticket.

Gets a value indicating whether a conflict occurred between the functionality supported by the printer and the functionality requested in the initial merger of two source <xref href="System.Printing.PrintTicket"></xref>s.
One of the <xref href="System.Printing.ConflictStatus"></xref> values that indicates either that no conflict occurred or that at least one conflict occurred but was resolved.
The default is <xref href="System.Printing.ConflictStatus.NoConflict"></xref>.
Determines whether the specified <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> is equal to the current <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> to compare.
`true` if the <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> objects are equal; otherwise, `false`.
`false` is also returned if the object passed is not a <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref>.
Gets the hash code associated with the <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> and its <xref href="System.Printing.PrintTicket"></xref> and print stream.
A hash code for the current <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref>.
Determines if the specified <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> objects are equal.
The first <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> to compare.
The second <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> to compare.
`true` if the <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> objects are equal; otherwise, `false`.
Determines if the specified <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> objects are not equal.
The first <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> to compare.
The second <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> to compare.
`true` if the <xref href="System.Printing.ValidationResult"></xref> objects are not equal; otherwise, `false`.

Gets a <xref href="System.Printing.PrintTicket"></xref> object that results from the merging of two <xref href="System.Printing.PrintTicket"></xref> objects, which might have been adjusted to ensure its viability.
A valid and viable <xref href="System.Printing.PrintTicket"></xref>.
The default is `null`.
